      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 id="switch-night-mode">Switch Night-Mode</h2>
<p>The best part is the night-mode that comes with this theme. Once you click on night-mode, the website remebers it untill you close or toggle!</p>

<h2 id="installation">Installation</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Fork the repository</li>
  <li>Go to settings and set Github Pages source as master.</li>
  <li>Your new site should be ready at https://username.github.io/hagura/</li>
</ul>

<p>Default theme will look like this</p>

<p><img src="http://webjeda.com/hagura/images/hagura-1.png" alt="webjeda hagura jekyll theme" /></p>

<p>Switch to Dark Theme</p>

<p><img src="http://webjeda.com/hagura/images/hagura-dark-jekyll-theme.png" alt="webjeda hagura dark jekyll theme" /></p>

<p>This theme is responsive.</p>

<p><img src="http://webjeda.com/hagura/images/hagura-responsive.png" alt="webjeda hagura responsive jekyll theme" /></p>

<h2 id="development">Development</h2>
<p>Make changes to the <strong>master</strong> branch and create a pull request. Do not use <strong>gh-pages</strong> branch as it is used to host the theme.</p>

